<subSubSection id="FDAA651F062E2E62FF48FCF4FB892753" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B50F3694062E2E62FF48FCF4FB892753" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,2035]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86062E2E62FF48FCF4FEA424BF" bold="true" box="[199,334,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name for this new species acknowledges the Dambimangari, traditional owners of Camden Sound, where the species was first discovered. It is a noun used in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
